{{!--
  FILE: views/about.handlebars
  PURPOSE: About page – rendered automatically by autoRender middleware.

  TEACHING NOTE:
    There is NO explicit router.get('/about', ...) in public.routes.js.
    This page is served entirely by the autoRender middleware because:
      1. GET /about reaches the router
      2. Explicit routes (/posts/:slug etc.) don't match /about
      3. autoRender checks: does views/about.handlebars exist? Yes → render it.

    This demonstrates that adding a new simple page only requires creating
    a new .handlebars file — no JavaScript code changes needed.
--}}
<article class="prose">
  <h1>About This Blog</h1>

  <p>
    This is a teaching demonstration project for <strong>INF653</strong>,
    showing how to build a scalable, route-driven application with
    Express.js and Handlebars.
  </p>

  <h2>What You'll Learn</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>SEO-friendly URL design with named route parameters</li>
    <li>Subdomain routing with <code>vhost</code></li>
    <li>Middleware chaining at the route level</li>
    <li>Scalable folder structure (routes / middleware / controllers / views)</li>
    <li>Automatic view rendering based on URL path</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> Node.js</li>
    <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Express.js 4</li>
    <li><strong>Templates:</strong> Handlebars (express-handlebars)</li>
    <li><strong>Subdomain routing:</strong> vhost</li>
  </ul>
</article>
